With a few ingredients, making a delicious passionfruit cake is easy. Ingredients  Lemon syrup  Preparation Step 1 Preheat the oven to 180°C/350°. Grease and lightly flour a 24cm pan. Step 2 Strain your passionfruit seeds over a jug to get the seeds and the juice separately. Reserve juice for cake mixture, and seeds for lemon syrup. Step 3 Beat butter, rind, and sugar in a small bowl with a mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs, before adding in milk and passionfruit juice. Add in the sifted flour in two batches. And combine. Step 4 Pour the mixture into the pan. Then bake the cake for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Step 5 Leave cake in the pan for 5 minutes before turning it onto a wire rack placed over a tray. Step 6 To make the lemon syrup, place sugar, lemon juice, water, and half the reserved passionfruit seeds in a small saucepan. Stir over heat, without boiling, until sugar dissolves. Step 7 Pour hot syrup over hot cake; serve cake warm or freeze for later use.